Put the lemon zest and juice in a large bowl, making sure you remove any pips. Add the berries and mash into a purée using a potato masher. Pour in the condensed milk.In a separate large bowl, pour in the cream and whisk using an electric hand whisk or balloon whisk, until soft peaks form and curl over a little when you lift the whisk out of the mixture. Make sure you don’t whisk past this point.Pour the fruit purée into the cream and carefully mix together using a big spoon, until the mixture is all the same colour.Spoon the mixture into a large tub and cover with a lid or cling film. Freeze for at least 4 hours, or overnight.